Daudu Galadanchi, an actor in Nigeria's Northern film industry, Kannywood, has died at 86. Galadanchi died in Kano on Wednesday night and was buried according to Islamic rites on Thursday in Rangaza, Ungoggo Local Government Area of the state. The thespian was born in 1934 and attended Kano Middle School in 1942. He gained prominence for his roles in movies where he acted as a judge.